What is SeaweedSeaweedsa marine form of algaeare found in all the earth s oceanin all climate zones from the warm seas of the tropics to the cold waters of the Arctic and Antarcticyet they remain something of a mysteryThe global distribution of seaweeds has not been comprehensively mappedthe full details of their habitats are unknowntheir taxonomic classification is incomplete and their biodiversity is not yet understoodBut there are reckoned to be about 10 000 kinds of seaweed in the worldand they are essential to the life of the planetAlthough we think the oxygen we breathe comes from land plantsmarine algae of all sizes provide some 75 percent of the planet s oxygen supply through photosynthesisand absorb a huge amount of atmospheric carbon dioxideAnd as noted by Darwinseaweeds play a foundation role in marine ecosystemsproviding food and shelter for many marine organisms and for the people and animals that live on themSee Global Seaweed NetworkNatural History Museumwww nhm ac ukThe Aquatic Biomewww ucmp berkeley eduwww microbeworld  Photo yoohere

Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C seaweedsnackohmygimomgplantbasedlunchsnackseavegetableseaveggiesveganhandyfoodfoodwhimsypictureperfectsharingsavourysnacknewraw glutenfreemonocleketodietmediterraneandietmemeskidsnacksnackingwellposhpremixtravelsnacksgimhealthforallqualitysnackorganicsnackpremiumsnacksnackingwellschoolsnacksgourmetsnacks

Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C

SEED SEAWEEDSLIM JIMSRECIPEOkaythis might be my most bonkers recipe to dateBut it is soo good Those of you in the US will know what Slim Jims areBasically they are highly processed but delicious beef jerky snack sticksI saw mention of seaweed Slim Jims somewhere ages agobut with no recipeIt s kind of haunted me ever sinceTodaya horrendously rainy dayI had a goSee what you thinkIt s quite saltybut has loads of flavour and a nicely chewy textureIf you ve got some nori sheets kicking aroundgo raid your seeds and spices give this a goHave you ever had a Slim JimSeed and Seaweed Slim Jims 50g pumpkin seeds 50g sunflower seeds toasted in 160Cfan 350F oven for 20 minutes1 2 tsp onion powder1 4 tsp white pepper1 tsp smoked paprika or 1 2 tsp Liquid Smokemore to taste after mixing 1 tsp low sodium vegetable stock powderoptional 2 tsp nutritional yeast1 2 tsp cayenne1 tsp coconut aminos or low sodium soy sauce1 tsp blackstrap molasses black treacle1 2 tsp vinegar1 2 tsp crushed toasted fennel seeds2 sheets of nori seaweedcut in half across across widest side Add all spices flavourings to a small food processor and mixAdd the toasted seeds and blitz to coarse sand textureYou want to be able to squish it into smallthin sausagesit will still crumble a bit piecing it together if needs bePut a strip of squished filling across one of the cut nori sheetswetting the edges of the sheets with waterRoll up tightlysmoothing endsCut into piecesDo remainderLet dry out before storing in a lidded container at room tempLow carbhigh proteinvegan veganjerkyseaweednoriseaweedsnacklowcarbideasveganlowcarbinstasnackswholefoodiewholefoodsnacks

Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C

SoI don t know about youbut I m pretty much always wanting to snackI especially live for savory snacks because salty goodness is where it s atI teamed up withAnnieChunsInc to bring you this delicious sesame seaweed popcornit s a perfect healthier snack that really delivers on flavor ad First make a toasted sesame seed andAnnieChunsInc Sesame Seaweed Snack seasoning blendthen pop some popcorndouse it in a drizzle of vegan buttersaltand add seasoning to taste If you make the sesame seaweed seasoning in advance then its sesame seaweed popcorn snack whenever you wantEasy snacking is at your fingertipsOkI know you re all craving popcorn nowso here s the recipe Ingredients 1 packageanniechunsinc Sesame Seaweed Snack1 tbsp toasted sesame seeds3 tbsp refined coconut oil or canola oil1 3 cup popcorn kernels1 2 tbsp melted vegan butterto tasteSalt to tasteDirections 1Crumble the seaweed snacks in a spice grindersmall food processoror using a mortar and pestleTransfer to a small bowlThen grind the toasted sesame seeds until they are slightly chopped up but still have textureMix the sesame seeds into the crumbled seaweed snack 2In a large pot with a lid add the 3 tablespoons of oil along with just 3 popcorn kernelsHeat over medium heat until the oil is hot and you hear the popcorn pop 3Add the rest of the popcorn kernels and cover the potRemove the pot from the heat and wait for about 30 secondsthen place the pot back over the heat 4Shake the pot while it is over the stove and wait to hear the popcorn popOnce the popcorn has stopped poppingturn off the heat and remove the popcornDrizzle over the melted vegan butter and add the sesame seaweed seasoning to tasteat least of the mixture and up to all of itSalt the popcorn to taste and enjoyanniechunspopcornhealthysnacksnackseaweedsnacksesamepopcornvegansnack

Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C seaweedsnackvegetarianseaweedplantbasedlunchsnackseaveggiesveganpictureperfectsharingwhyOMGOhMyGimlunchglutenfreeOMGketodietmediterraneandietharrodsfoodhallkidsnacksnackingwellALGENtravelsnacksgimhealthforallqualitysnackALGAECuriosityTakesYouFurthersnackingwellschoolsnacksAnimalFriendly

Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C

OhMy Gim for youBenefits of eating OMG Seaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C

What is SeaweedSeaweedsa marine form of algaeare found in all the earth s oceanin all climate zones from the warm seas of the tropics to the cold waters of the Arctic and Antarcticyet they remain something of a mysteryThe global distribution of seaweeds has not been comprehensively mappedthe full details of their habitats are unknowntheir taxonomic classification is incomplete and their biodiversity is not yet understoodBut there are reckoned to be about 10 000 kinds of seaweed in the worldand they are essential to the life of the planetAlthough we think the oxygen we breathe comes from land plantsmarine algae of all sizes provide some 75 percent of the planet s oxygen supply through photosynthesisand absorb a huge amount of atmospheric carbon dioxideAnd as noted by Darwinseaweeds play a foundation role in marine ecosystemsproviding food and shelter for many marine organisms and for the people and animals that live on themSee Global Seaweed NetworkNatural History Museumwww nhm ac ukThe Aquatic Biomewww ucmp berkeley eduwww microbeworld  oasis

Plantbased revolutionThe growing popularity of a plantbased diet is the most important food trend in 2019Due to rising awareness of the cost of eating too many animalbased foodsconsumers are converting to plantbased foodsSeaweed is the ultimate in plantbased foodHEALTHY BENEFITS OF GIM roasted seaweed 1High in iodineRoasted Gimseaweed or any type of seaweed for that matteris a rich source of iodineIodine is a mineral that is essential for your metabolism and helps your thyroid gland to function the way it should beOne sheet of gim contains around half of the daily recommended intake of iodine 2Source of vitamin B12Vitamin B12 supports normal functioning of the brain and nervous system and helps form red blood cellsGim contains 1 2 mg vitamin B12 per 1 sheet 3High in potassiumPotassium is a mineral that helps lower your blood pressure and lowers your risk of stroke and heart diseaseGim contains 50 mg of potassium per 1 sheet 4Contains protein and fiberWhile the amounts are not super highroasted seaweed does actually contain protein and fiber 5Low in calories and saturated fatRoasted seaweed is incredibly low in calories with one sheet containing only 5 calories or lessThe amount of fat in gim is almost negligible 6Delicious tasteOkay this may not necessarily be a health benefitbut the delicious taste of roasted seaweed makes it so much easier to eat as a healthy afternoon snackThe taste is very unique and is hard to compare with anything else It s worth mentioning that roasted seaweed chips are also a very good source of calciumphosphorusmagnesium and vitamin C
